================================================================================
1. DEFINITIONS
================================================================================

  "Toolkit" means this repository as a product: the Compose Desktop client,
  Kotlin generator (:core / :cli), templates distributed as part of the
  framework, documentation, scripts, and related tooling — i.e. Nexus itself
  when used, sold, or redistributed as a generation / scaffolding product.

  "Derived Work" (or "Generated Work") means any project, application,
  binary, or other material produced by running the Toolkit's generation
  pipeline, or by adapting the bundled templates into an application you
  build and ship.

  "Commercial Use of the Toolkit" means selling, licensing for a fee,
  offering as paid SaaS, or otherwise commercially exploiting the Toolkit
  itself (or a substantial portion of it) as a product or service.

  "Revenue-Producing Use" means any use of a Derived Work that produces
  revenue, including but not limited to: selling the app, charging for
  access or features, paid SaaS, advertising monetization tied to the app,
  or otherwise commercializing the Derived Work for profit.

  "Commercial Institution Use" means deploying or using a Derived Work
  inside or for a company, for-profit organization, commercial workplace,
  or other commercial institutional context (even if that particular
  deployment does not itself charge end users).

  "Authorization Period" means the period from 2026-07-21 through
  2041-07-21 inclusive (fifteen years from the clock start date).

  "You" means any person or entity exercising rights under this License.

